            <h1>Commands</h1>
            <p>Example command usage: <code>php app/commands/bin.php myCommand option1 option2</code></p>
            <p>Help command: <code>php app/commands/bin.php myCommand help</code></p>

            <hr>

            <h2>Available commands</h2>
            <code>create:controller controllername</code> - Creates a new controller<br>
            <hr>
            <h2>Example commands</h2>
            <code>php app/commands/bin.php create:controller home</code>
            <p>Why write home? Because automatically it will create a controller with the name HomeController So if you want to create a controller with the name <code>MyController</code> you have to write <code>php app/commands/bin.php create:controller my</p>


